rial that ends in $6.5 billion settlement 1998 as a result of minnesota trial a $206 billion master national settlement is brokered 1998 co authors major jama article with dr richard hunt of the mayo clinic detailing corrupt scientific practices in the tobacco industry 1998 asked by director general of the world health organization to help create the who framework convention on tobacco control 1998 charter member of national academy of sciences nas committee on science technology and law 1999 2002 co chairs group that builds support for stanford's interdisciplinary bio x program 2000 described by upside magazine as one of 100 people who have changed the world 2002 2009 appointed senior associate dean for faculty & academic affairs in the school of engineering 2002 leads drive to create a new department of bioengineering at stanford 2003 becomes a director of startup theranos systems founded by former student elizabeth holmes bio x logo 2003 stanford's james h clark center opens as home for the bio x program 2004 named yumi and yasunori kaneko family university fellow in undergraduate education 2005 world health organization framework convention on tobacco control takes effect 2007 joins national academy of science nas committee to examine the state of forensic evidence and testimony in the united states 2009 co authors nas report calling for complete overhaul of how forensic analysis is conducted in the us 2009 awarded lloyd w dinkelspiel award for distinctive contributions to undergraduate education 2011 appointed professor emeritus stay connected itunes icon google+ icon facebook icon twitter icon linkedin icon stanford university school of engineering 475 via ortega stanford california 94305 4121 650.725 1575 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved accreditation info terms of use copyright complaints contact us
